Here at BBN we modified the ISI domain server code to include a field
in the internally stored RR called RESTRICTION.  When the server is
replying to a query, it filters the returned RR's on the RESTRICTION
field as a function of where the query originated from.  We
implemented 4 RESTRICTION levels which we thought would be useful:

        RESTRICTION     Meaning
        -----------     -------
        ANY             Any querying host can see this RR.
        INZONE          Only querying hosts that reside in the
                        server's zone of authority can see this
                        RR.
        CORESIDENT      Only a coresident resolver may see this
                        RR (ie. query originated from same host).
        UNAVAILABLE     No hosts may see this RR.

John.

